<br>
Its an addition to an old game, not really a "new" game... only reason I got SoL was because I had to upgrade without it no matter if I wanted to or not.  So it only made sense to go the whole nine yards since I had to jump through hoops even if I wasnt ready for the new expansion.<br>
<br>
If I wanted "a new game" I'd have gotten an upgrade so I could play DaoC, but I was happy with this... just the way it was.<br>
<br>
Im not really pissed about the whole situation and the changes that had to be made, in fact Im a lot more satisfied than I thought i would be.  But I know a lot of people who cannot afford to upgrade to the minimum requirements and I think its sad that they're being forced to quit.  I thought I needed a new video card but ends up they did a small patch which improved the visibility, all is good for me now.  If I would have had to purchase a new video card I wouldnt have continued playing... no matter how much I "wanted to play a new game".<br>
<br>
My friends keep asking "is it worth it?" and so far Im not so sure if I want to encourage them to spend the money to be able to continue playing.  Not everyone can afford top of the line, new computer parts, and or upgrades anytime they want... some people can barely afford to squeeze the cost of internet access and game fees in their budget and now the one "reasonable" form of entertainment they had in their life is hanging on a line and they're going "damn, this sucks" and everyone else is trying to make it seem like Verant is doing them a favor.  I am just a bit biased I guess.<br>
<br>
