Ok seriously, as long as this is a performance rant, here goes:<br>
Athlon 1 Ghz<br>
Win 98 SE<br>
256 mB Ram<br>
gForce 2 PRO<br>
56k dialup (yuck)<br>
<br>
Conclusion: unplayable. Video choppyness makes death a certainty in any underground zone where you cant do 3 or 4 spins to get all the textures to preload. LGuk, turn a corner = death. Zonetime is > 5 minutes normally, well over that into a crowded zone. The trip from Guk to East Commons took about 40 minutes realtime. Yuck yuck yuck.<br>
<br>
This PC should run this program just fine. I blame the application. It seems I may be right, as there are several framerate fixes in the patches that I do not have yet. More memory is INC as well. We'll see.<br>
